[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Technical Stack Requirements

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-001
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Programming Language
STATEMENT: The system shall be developed using TypeScript.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-002
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Runtime Environment
STATEMENT: The system shall run on Node.js version 22 or higher.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-003
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Package Manager
STATEMENT: The project shall use PNPM with Workspace support for dependency management.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-004
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Build Tooling
STATEMENT: The project shall use Tsdown as the bundler.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-005
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Code Quality - Linter
STATEMENT: The project shall use Oxlint for linting.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-006
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Code Quality - Formatter
STATEMENT: The project shall use Oxfmt for code formatting.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-007
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Testing
STATEMENT: The project shall use Vitest as the test runner.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-008
STATUS: Active
TITLE: CI/CD
STATEMENT: The project shall use GitHub Actions for continuous integration and deployment.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-009
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Version Control
STATEMENT: The project shall use GitHub for version control.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-010
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Task Management
STATEMENT: The project shall use GitHub Issues and GitHub Projects for task management.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-011
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Documentation
STATEMENT: The project shall use the GitHub Repository Wiki for documentation.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TECH-012
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Requirements Engineering
STATEMENT: The project shall use StrictDoc for requirements engineering.

[[/SECTION]]
